 144:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   /* The SystemCoreClock variable is updated in three ways:
 145:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****       1) by calling CMSIS function SystemCoreClockUpdate()
 146:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****       2) by calling HAL API function HAL_RCC_GetHCLKFreq()
 147:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****       3) each time HAL_RCC_ClockConfig() is called to configure the system clock frequency
 148:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****          Note: If you use this function to configure the system clock; then there
 149:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****                is no need to call the 2 first functions listed above, since SystemCoreClock
 150:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****                variable is updated automatically.
 151:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   */
 152:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   uint32_t SystemCoreClock = HSI_VALUE;
 153:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c **** 
