 192:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c **** /**
 193:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   * @brief  Update SystemCoreClock variable according to Clock Register Values.
 194:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *         The SystemCoreClock variable contains the core clock (HCLK), it can
 195:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *         be used by the user application to setup the SysTick timer or configure
 196:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *         other parameters.
 197:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *
 198:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   * @note   Each time the core clock (HCLK) changes, this function must be called
 199:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *         to update SystemCoreClock variable value. Otherwise, any configuration
 200:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *         based on this variable will be incorrect.
 201:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *
 202:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   * @note   - The system frequency computed by this function is not the real
 203:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *           frequency in the chip. It is calculated based on the predefined
 204:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *           constant and the selected clock source:
 205:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *
 206:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *           - If SYSCLK source is HSI, SystemCoreClock will contain the HSI_VALUE(**)
 207:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *
 208:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *           - If SYSCLK source is HSE, SystemCoreClock will contain the HSE_VALUE(***)
 209:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *
 210:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *           - If SYSCLK source is PLL, SystemCoreClock will contain the HSE_VALUE(***)
 211:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *             or HSI_VALUE(*) multiplied/divided by the PLL factors.
 212:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *
 213:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *         (**) HSI_VALUE is a constant defined in stm32g4xx_hal.h file (default value
 214:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *              16 MHz) but the real value may vary depending on the variations
 215:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *              in voltage and temperature.
 216:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *
 217:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *         (***) HSE_VALUE is a constant defined in stm32g4xx_hal.h file (default value
 218:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *              24 MHz), user has to ensure that HSE_VALUE is same as the real
 219:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *              frequency of the crystal used. Otherwise, this function may
 220:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *              have wrong result.
 221:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *
 222:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *         - The result of this function could be not correct when using fractional
 223:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *           value for HSE crystal.
 224:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   *
 225:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   * @param  None
 226:./Src/Drivers/CMSIS/Device/ST/STM32G4xx/Source/Templates/system_stm32g4xx.c ****   * @retval None
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccvsirLi.s 			page 6


